Diagnosis
. Pronotum rather opaque (
Fig. 63
); FLP sclerite subapicodorsal lobe strongly produced anteriorly (
Figs. 159–160
); right lateral fold produced into a longitudinal spoon-shape process with apical portion open ventrally, ventral edge with a brush of minute villi, lacking well-sclerotized projection on apicoventral edge (
Fig. 160
); axial sclerite shorter than subaxial sclerite, acute apically (
Figs. 159–160
); subaxial sclerite long and thin (
Fig. 160
).
